<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-04-09T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-04-09T14:00:00-05:00" n="635" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d635">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/314: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-09T14:00:00-05:00">April 9, 1929—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>47. Legation’s eighty-nine, April 8, 9 a.m. The Department assumes that
                            you have conveyed to President Moncada the assurances given by the
                            Brigade Commander as reported in the last paragraph of your
                            telegram.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>